                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d505">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/769: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-08-08T18:00:00+01:00"
                            >August 8, 1935—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 8—2 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>455. My 488, August 6, 6 p.m., paragraph 2.<note n="50" xml:id="d505fn50">Not
                        printed.</note> I understand from British sources that the conference
                    between the representatives of France, Great Britain and Italy will take place
                    on August 15th presumably at Paris and that as the conversations are to take
                    place in France an invitation will be sent by Laval to the Italian Government to
                    send a representative. It is stated that Laval and Eden will represent their
                    respective Governments and that presumably the Italians will send Aloisi.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
